cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.MM 

This paper deals with the problem of fine-grained image recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a framework that incorporates professional knowledge into deep neural network architectures, which falls under the scope of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of a graph neural network for knowledge representation also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques for organizing the knowledge graph, which could place it under the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the experiments involve the use of a widely used dataset for bird classification, which could suggest the paper belonging to the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM).
